          </div>
          <ul class="mt10">
            <li class="list-num">Design the installation based on heat-load calculations according to the site’s climate and insulation conditions.</li>
            <li class="list-num">Confirm the maximum power by application and the available incoming capacity (upgrade if incoming power is insufficient).</li>
            <li class="list-num">Remove any nicks or sharp edges that could damage the heating cable. </li>
            <li class="list-num">Ensure hydrostatic testing of pipes/tanks is complete and fully dry; remove surface contaminants.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="title-wrap relative mt60">
            <h3 class="inline-block pr20 f20 line2">Precautions during construction</h3>
          </div>
          <ul class="mt10">
            <li class="list-num">When installing on piping, wrap GLASS TAPE at 30–50 cm intervals; at bends, curves and irregularities, wrap firmly so the heating cable is in tight contact.</li>
            <li class="list-num">Seal the cable end terminals with a waterproof heat-shrink tube or an End Seal Kit for insulation and waterproofing.</li>
            <li class="list-num">Do not pull the cable with excessive force or kink it during work.</li>
            <li class="list-num">A temperature sensor must be installed during subsequent processes such as insulation work.</li>
            <li class="list-num">Do not cross-install heating cables.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="title-wrap relative mt60">
            <h3 class="inline-block pr20 f20 line2">Post-construction precautions</h3>
          </div>
          <ul class="mt10">
            <li class="list-num">Verify and inspect that installation followed the specification (visual and resistance tests).</li>
            <li class="list-num">After applying power to the heating cable, perform a heating test.</li>
            <li class="list-num">Check control panel operating status.</li>
            <li class="list-num">Confirm proper installation and operation with the customer/client.</li>
          </ul>
